{"summary":"Reviewed five amendments. Four identify real correctness or robustness issues worth fixing; the timeout-test amendment misreads the implementation and does not establish an actual defect.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-17-fd63d152","decision":"accept","rationale":"Prior-cycle entries in `retryable_failed_attempts` become unreachable once `current_cycle` advances because lookups are keyed by `(stage, cycle)`. The map is local and the growth is bounded, but pruning stale entries on `CycleAdvanced` is a safe, low-risk cleanup that avoids carrying dead state through long journal replays."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-a210d3ba","decision":"accept","rationale":"`apply_jitter` currently derives jitter from `SystemTime::now().subsec_nanos() % 1000`, which is heavily time-correlated and can collapse to identical values when calls are closely spaced or clock granularity is coarse. That weakens the thundering-herd mitigation jitter is supposed to provide, so the randomness source should be improved."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-3303d1eb","decision":"reject","rationale":"The amendment's premise does not match the code. `ManagedChild::wait()` is not a blocking OS wait future; it polls `try_wait()` and sleeps on `CHILD_WAIT_POLL_INTERVAL`, and `confirm_teardown()` is likewise timer-based. With `start_paused`, this test is intentionally compatible with Tokio's paused-time model, so the claimed dependence on fragile `wait()`/EOF behavior is not established."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-b2220aa1","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real resume-state bug. `derive_resume_state` records retryable failures when `will_retry=true`, but it never removes that entry when the same stage later fails terminally with `will_retry=false`. On resume, the stale entry incorrectly advances to the old retry count instead of restarting at attempt 1 after a terminal failure."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-39fd79cd","decision":"accept","rationale":"In the retry path, the durable `stage_failed` journal entry is appended before the pre-backoff snapshot write. If that snapshot write is only warned on and the process dies during backoff, the journal records a retrying failure while `run.json` can remain `Running`, and `run resume` rejects that state. That undermines the purpose of the pre-backoff snapshot."}]}